This program does the following:
- Creates a `TriangleOsc` object which generates a triangle wave.
- Connects it to the DAC (digital-to-analog converter) for audio output.
- Sets the frequency to 261.63 Hz (middle C).
- Runs for exactly 1 second.
- Stops the oscillator afterward.

You can run this in the ChucK environment (e.g., chuck command line or chuck GUI) to hear a one-second triangle wave at middle C.

Note: If you want to be more precise about the timing, you can also use `dac => gain => null;` or control gain, but for basic playback, the above is sufficient and standard.

